Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. 
Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice the @yellow onion{1}. Mince the @garlic{2%cloves}. 
Finely chop the @chives{1/4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @Portobello mushrooms{8%ounce}(thinly sliced). 
Trim and discard the bottom inch from the @asparagus{6%ounce}, then cut into 1-inch pieces. 
Core, seed, and cut the @red bell pepper{1} into 1-inch cubes.

== Cook the asparagus and pasta ==

Fill a large #bowl{} with ice water and set aside. Add asparagus to the boiling water 
for ~{2-3%minutes}, until bright green and crisp-tender. Remove with a #slotted spoon{} 
and place in the ice bath. Add the @orecchiette pasta{6%ounce} to the boiling water. 
Cook ~{9-11%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving ½ cup pasta water.

== Cook the mushrooms ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the mushrooms. 
Cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until golden brown. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 
Remove from the pan and set aside.

== Cook the peppers and onions ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in the same pan over medium heat. Add the onion 
and bell pepper. Cook, tossing, for ~{6-8%minutes}, until slightly caramelized. Add the 
garlic and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste). Cook ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. 
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Toss ==

Add the pasta to the pan along with the mushrooms, asparagus, @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, 
@Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, half the chives, and a splash of the reserved pasta water. Toss 
over medium heat for ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Finish ==

Serve the portobello and orecchiette primavera sprinkled with the remaining chives and enjoy!